OL,3,CStarmer in the 'endgame' of his time
OL,4,Cin office as pressure grows on him to
OL,5,Cquit
OL,7,FThere has been a drip, drip, drip of
OL,8,FMPs and junior ministerial aides
OL,9,Fcalling on the PM to set a timetable
OL,10,Ffor his departure since he gave his "I-
OL,11,Fam-not-budging" speech this morning.
OL,13,FThis was not Keir Starmer's plan. And
OL,14,Falthough the dam hasn't yet burst,
OL,15,Fministers tell me that we are in "the
OL,16,Fend game" of his time in office, and
OL,17,Fhe will not be able to resist the
OL,18,Fpressure.
OL,26,@rD@eOUsD@OO]wD@bOUxD@IO]
