OL,3,CStarmer in the 'endgame' of his time
OL,4,Cin office as pressure grows on him to
OL,5,Cquit
OL,7,FThey think the fact that no top member
OL,8,Fof his team has come out in support of
OL,9,Fhim tonight may mean that they will
OL,10,Facquire the backbone to deliver the
OL,11,Fbitter-tasting message to him.
OL,13,FAnd if they don't, it is likely to get
OL,14,Fmessy very fast. "Ministers will
OL,15,Fresign," said one. It may feel like
OL,16,Fthe catastrophic last days of Boris
OL,17,FJohnson, when so many of his ministers
OL,18,Fquit.
OL,26,@vD@ROUwD@HO]
